<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 01 at 11:47PM CDT until May 02 at 2:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1215 AM CDT
FOR EAST CENTRAL CARSON AND SOUTHWESTERN GRAY COUNTIES...
At 1147 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles southwest
of Lefors, or 12 miles south of Pampa, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible. Hail
damage to vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
White Deer, Lefors, Kingsmill and Lake Mcclellan.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
